-- U.S. 2012 Foreign-Securities Holdings Rose 16%, Treasury Says
-- B y   K a s i a   K l i m a s i n s k a
-- 2013-08-30T20:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-30/u-s-2012-foreign-securities-holdings-rose-16-treasury-says.html
U.S. investors boosted their
holdings of foreign securities last year by 16.1 percent to
$7.94 trillion from a year earlier, led by purchases of
equities, Treasury Department data showed today.  Portfolio holdings of U.K. assets topped the list at $1.13
trillion as of Dec. 31, followed by $808 billion of Canadian
securities and $784 billion in the  Cayman Islands . Of the total
holdings, 67 percent were equities, 29 percent in long-term debt
and the rest were short-term debt instruments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kasia Klimasinska in Washington at 
